					<td valign="top">
<B CLASS="HeadlineText">Server Outage Planned - UPDATED</B><BR><BR><P>
<HR>
On Tuesday, August 26th, at 3AM Pacific, (-7:00 UTC), all EverQuest worlds will be brought down for a scheduled update. The estimated downtime is 7 hours. <BR><BR>-The SOE Game Operations Team 
<P></P>
<P>
<HR>

<P></P>
<H1>Upcoming for August 26th, 2003</H1>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p><FONT face=Arial></FONT></o:p></P>
<P></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><FONT face=Arial><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Plane of Mischief changes going to the Legends.</B><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The Plane of Mischief, home of the trickster Bristlebane, has undergone an extensive revamp.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>As one of the most unusual places to visit in EverQuest, this zone will be a very interesting challenge, if you have a sturdy funny bone.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Partial Zone Revamps coming to all servers.</B><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>These changes are not as dramatic as those made to the Plane of Mischief, but they are great improvements to these zones that needed only a little modification to make them much better.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>The zones we'll be updating this week are: The Deep, Charasis (Howling Stones), Dragon Necropolis, Siren's Grotto, The Hole, The City of Mist, The Accursed Temple of Cazic-Thule and Velketor's Labyrinth.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Gameplay in these zones has been improved, based on feedback from players and careful review of the content.<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><FONT face=Arial><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">New filters and chat message options will be added.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></B>We will be separating pet melee messages into their own category.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>You will be able to send them to whichever chat window you want, or filter them out completely in the Options window.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We have also added the ability to send /random messages to any chat window you'd like.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>There is no option to filter these messages, however, to prevent any loss of the information in cases where it is needed.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Memorizing spell sets.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN></B>We will be adding /memspellset # to make memorizing spells a bit less bothersome. <SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</SPAN>Using this command will memorize one of your saved spell sets.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN># is the number or name (or shortened name) of the spell set you wish to memorize.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Note that if you use a shortened version of the spell set name, it will match the first spell set that has those characters, so /memspellset Dots will find your "Dots and Charms", or "Dots", or "Dotsandstuff" - whichever shows up first on your list.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Shared Bank gains a Plat slot.</B><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We will be adding a Platinum slot to the shared bank to make transactions between characters on the same account more convenient.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial><B style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">Rain Spells can be deadly.</B><SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>Rain Spells have been resisted 100% of the time when an NPC was above level 20 and had less than 10% of its hit points left.<SPAN style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp; </SPAN>We will be removing this restriction.<o:p></o:p></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><FONT face=Arial>Also, as a heads up to players that have created their own user interfaces for EverQuest, these are the interface files that we expect to change next week.</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face=Arial>** UI Files **</FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><o:p><FONT face=Arial>&nbsp;</FONT></o:p></P>
